    ],
    "lyrics": {
      "text": "O_ ho-ly Mar-tyrs, who have con-test-ed well and have been crowned: In-ter-cede ye with the Lord that He have mer-cy on__ our__ souls. \n\nGlo-ry to Thee, O Christ__ God, the boast of the A-pos--tles, the joy of the Mar--tyrs, who pro-claimed the con-sub-stan-tial Trin--i--ty. \n\n\n\nDance,__ O E-sai-as; the Vir-gin hath con-ceived in her womb and hath giv-en birth__ to a Son, Em-ma-nu-el, Who is both God and man; O-ri-ent is His Name. In mag-ni-fy-ing Him, we call the Vir-gin__ blest."
    }
  }
